  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Providing life-saving humanitarian assistance including protection, emergency shelter and winter support for undocumented Afghan returnees from Iran</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IOM aims to prioritise support to a wider range of Persons with Specific Needs (PSNs) and families with a tailored package of assistance including direct protection assistance, cash transfers, and/or NFIs to 18,000 individuals, cash for transportation, escorted return services to places of origin, creation of a help desk for women and children, and a women&#x2019;s shelter. Facilities at the border will be improved to ensure screening are more comprehensive and vulnerable persons seeking assistance are not overlooked. IOM will also implement protection-enhanced Flow Monitoring Survey modules to ensure comprehensive information on the needs of the returnee population are captured in Milak.</narrative>
  </description>
